(43, 3, 19, 43, 8, 12, 12, 'light is come into the world', 'Light and Darkness Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between light and darkness. John 3:19 discusses how men loved darkness, while John 8:12 presents Jesus as the light of the world, indicating a choice between following light or remaining in darkness.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 19, 53, 2, 12, 12, 'loved darkness rather than light', 'Condemnation and Unrighteousness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of rejecting light and truth, highlighting a preference for darkness and unrighteousness. This connection illustrates the moral choice between light and evil deeds.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 19, 43, 9, 39, 41, 'light is come into the world', 'Light and Blindness Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between light and darkness, as well as sight and blindness. John 3:19 discusses how people prefer darkness due to their evil deeds, while John 9:39-41 highlights the judgment of those who claim to see but are spiritually blind.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 19, 45, 2, 8, 8, 'loved darkness rather than light', 'Light and Darkness Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the choice between light and unrighteousness. John 3:19 highlights the preference for darkness due to evil deeds, while Romans 2:8 addresses those who obey unrighteousness, indicating a rejection of truth.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 19, 45, 1, 32, 32, 'men loved darkness rather than light', 'Condemnation of Evil Deeds', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of evil actions and the preference for darkness over light. John 3:19 highlights that men loved darkness because their deeds were evil, while Romans 1:32 states that those who commit such things are worthy of death.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 19, 61, 3, 3, 3, 'loved darkness rather than light', 'Light and Darkness Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between light and darkness, with John 3:19 highlighting the preference for darkness due to evil deeds, while 2 Peter 3:3 describes scoffers pursuing their own lusts. This connection highlights the moral choices individuals make in response to truth.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 19, 42, 12, 47, 47, 'men loved darkness rather than light', 'Condemnation and Accountability', 'This connection highlights the theme of accountability for one''s actions. Both passages emphasize the consequences of choosing darkness or failing to act according to one''s knowledge of good.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 20, 49, 5, 11, 13, 'light', 'Light and Darkness Contrast', 'Both passages emphasize the opposition between light and darkness. John 3:20 highlights that those who do evil avoid the light, while Ephesians 5:11-13 encourages reproving the unfruitful works of darkness, indicating that light reveals hidden deeds.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 20, 43, 7, 7, 7, NULL, 'Connection of Light and Evil', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of evil works and the rejection of light. In John 3:20, those who do evil avoid the light, while in John 7:7, Jesus states that the world hates him for testifying that its works are evil.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 20, 18, 24, 13, 17, 'hateth the light', 'Connection of Light and Darkness', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of rebellion against the light and the evil deeds committed in darkness. John 3:20 highlights the avoidance of light by those who do evil, while Job 24:13-17 describes those who rebel against the light and commit their wrongdoings under the cover of darkness.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 20, 20, 1, 29, 29, 'hateth the light', 'Connection of Hatred and Knowledge', 'Both passages emphasize a rejection of light and knowledge, highlighting that those who do evil or hate knowledge avoid the truth. This connection illustrates a common theme of choosing darkness over enlightenment.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 20, 20, 4, 18, 18, 'the light', 'Light and Righteousness Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of light as a representation of righteousness. John 3:20 discusses the avoidance of light by those who do evil, while Proverbs 4:18 highlights the path of the just as a shining light.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 20, 59, 1, 23, 25, 'doeth evil hateth the light', 'Connection of Light and Action', 'This connection highlights the contrast between those who act in darkness and those who engage with the ''perfect law of liberty.'' Both passages emphasize the importance of being a doer rather than merely a hearer, suggesting that true engagement with the light leads to righteous actions.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 20, 11, 22, 8, 8, 'hateth the light', 'Hatred of the Light', 'This connection highlights the theme of hatred towards those who speak truth. In John 3:20, those who do evil hate the light, while in 1 Kings 22:8, King Ahab expresses hatred for Micaiah, who prophesies truth he does not want to hear.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 21, 62, 1, 6, 6, 'doeth truth', 'Connection of Truth and Light', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of truth in relation to light and darkness. John 3:21 speaks of coming to the light to manifest deeds wrought in God, while 1 John 1:6 warns against claiming fellowship with God while walking in darkness, indicating a lack of truth.', 'theme', 0.482, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 21, 19, 139, 23, 24, 'that his deeds may be made manifest', 'Connection of Seeking Truth', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of self-examination and coming to the light. John 3:21 speaks of deeds being made manifest, while Psalms 139:23-24 calls for God to search the heart and reveal any wickedness.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 21, 64, 1, 11, 11, NULL, 'Connection of Good and Evil', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between good and evil actions. John 3:21 highlights those who do truth and are of God, while 3 John 1:11 reinforces that doing good is indicative of being of God.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 21, 62, 4, 15, 16, 'doeth truth', 'Connection of Truth and Love', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between one''s actions and divine presence. The act of doing truth in John 3:21 parallels confessing Jesus in 1 John 4:15, suggesting that genuine faith manifests in love and truth.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 21, 19, 119, 105, 105, 'light', 'Light and Truth Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of light as a guide for righteous living. Both passages emphasize the importance of truth and divine guidance in one''s actions.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 21, 49, 5, 9, 9, 'doeth truth', 'Connection of Truth and Righteousness', 'This connection highlights the importance of truth in both passages. John 3:21 emphasizes coming to the light through truth, while Ephesians 5:9 mentions truth as part of the fruit of the Spirit, linking goodness and righteousness.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 21, 50, 2, 13, 13, 'wrought in God', 'Connection of Divine Work', 'Both passages emphasize that God is actively involved in the actions of believers. John 3:21 highlights that deeds are ''wrought in God,'' while Philippians 2:13 states that God works in believers to fulfill His purpose.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 22, 43, 4, 1, 3, 'baptized', 'Baptism and Discipleship Connection', 'This connection highlights the act of baptism as Jesus and his disciples engage in it in Judea, which leads to a notable increase in disciples. Both passages emphasize the significance of Jesus'' ministry and the growing number of followers, prompting his departure to Galilee.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 22, 43, 3, 26, 26, 'baptized', 'Connection of Baptism Practices', 'Both passages emphasize the act of baptizing. In John 3:22, Jesus is described as baptizing, while John 3:26 refers to Him as ''the same baptizeth.'' This connection highlights the significance of baptism in the ministry of both Jesus and John.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 22, 43, 7, 3, 3, 'into the land of Judea', 'Connection of Judea and Disciples', 'Both passages emphasize the location of Judea and the presence of Jesus'' disciples. In John 3:22, Jesus is actively baptizing in Judea, while John 7:3 mentions the disciples'' need to see Jesus'' works there.', 'theme', 0.307, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 22, 43, 2, 13, 13, NULL, 'Jesus'' Movement to Judea', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' journey to Jerusalem and Judea. John 2:13 introduces Jesus'' presence in Jerusalem during Passover, while John 3:22 shows his subsequent activities in Judea, indicating a continuity in his ministry.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 23, 26, 43, 2, 2, 'much water', 'Connection of Water Imagery', 'This connection highlights the significance of water in both passages. John 3:23 mentions ''much water'' for baptism, while Ezekiel 43:2 describes God''s voice as ''like a noise of many waters.''', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 23, 40, 3, 5, 6, 'much water there', 'Baptism in Water', 'Both passages emphasize the act of baptism occurring in locations with abundant water. John the Baptist is depicted as baptizing in Ænon and in the Jordan, highlighting the significance of water in the baptismal process.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 23, 41, 1, 4, 5, 'baptized', 'Baptism by John the Baptist', 'Both passages emphasize John baptizing people, highlighting his role in the ministry. The mention of baptism in both locations illustrates the significance of water in John''s practice.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 23, 42, 3, 7, 7, 'baptized', 'Baptism and Repentance Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the act of baptism as a significant event. John the Baptist''s call to the multitude in Luke highlights the urgency of repentance, which complements the baptizing activity mentioned in John.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 23, 1, 33, 18, 18, 'much water there', 'Connection of Locations and Water', 'Both passages emphasize locations associated with water. John baptizes in Ænon, which suggests a place of abundance, while Jacob arrives in Shalem, indicating a settlement in Canaan. This connection highlights the significance of water in both narratives.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
